<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7687&amp;p=77379#p77379"><![CDATA[
I had not thought of using CC65, but I like the idea of a non-Turing complete virtual machine. There are specific limitations that make the language and machine easier to implement, serialize and resume.<br /><br />Performance is not a big concern for me. The engine itself will be implemented in assembly. Only event response will be handled by the script, and the execution can be made to extend over several frames.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3706">qbradq</a> — Fri Apr 29, 2011 2:27 pm</p><hr />
